    <note>Xu Xuan [12236] Traces ancestry to Eastern Zhou and move from Donghai to Kuaiji. He was orphaned as a youth and his mother moved him and his younger brother, Kai, to her home in Hongzhou where he was buried in Hongzhou, Xinjian county (Western mountain [Xishan]). He had no sons. He received a nominal military office after he accomapnied the Li ruler when he submitted to Song. Xu Xuan, WJ, fulu, 1a ff. Are these Xu related to Xu Xi's Xiushui Xu, lineage? CBD, 3, 2002-4. 《唐代人物知識ベース》記其生卒年為：916 - 991.</note>
